    {
      "id": "3fd3fc46_b35df15d",
      "file_path": "cps-ri/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/spi/entities/FragmentEntity.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 84,
      "message": "problem is we have several Pojos for the same object (decoupled from DB). To prevent confusion about whether the object is a DB Entity of an PoJo we need to distinguish. Fragment is implemented by 2 different Pojos : Anchor and DataNode but for consistency we need to apply teh same naming pattern for all DB entities...",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
        "name": "Toine Siebelink",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "toine.siebelink@est.tech",
        "username": "ToineSiebelink"
      },
      "updated": "2020-11-30 16:38:40.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "837e75fe_e34183ad",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "b5ea0593_7f7b998d",
      "file_path": "cps-ri/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/spi/entities/FragmentEntity.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 84,
      "message": "usually pojos will be under some package e.g.pojos, and Entities on their specific packages as well. I agree with Ruslan and I dont see the need of renaming to *Entity\nIndeed entities are already under package \"entities\"",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6679,
        "name": "Claudio David Gasparini",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "gasparini24@gmail.com",
        "username": "cdgasparini"
      },
      "updated": "2020-11-30 18:24:29.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "3fd3fc46_b35df15d",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "d47b2160_6e87e603",
      "file_path": "cps-ri/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/spi/entities/FragmentEntity.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 84,
      "message": "For our internal state db we have the other way around: pojos at the controller level have the DTO suffix (ex: StateDto) and entities are kept as is (ex: State).\n\nSorry to bring another option to the table :(\n\nI'm not used to the Entity suffix. I like the idea to be able to quickly and easily identify the class with its name in the ide. That's being said, I still don't have a strong opinion.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
        "username": "brusak"
      },
      "updated": "2020-12-01 04:48:05.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "b5ea0593_7f7b998d",
      "unresolved": true
    },
